        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 3:38PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 337 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Oakland, or 10 miles north of Shaw Air Base, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts 40 to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bishopville, Lee State Park, Elliott, Mayesville, Lynchburg, Lucknow,
Ashwood, Oswego, Dalzell, Dinkins Mill, Manville, Spring Hill,
Antioch, Boykin, St. Charles, Rembert, Wisacky, Woodrow, and Shiloh.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 98 and 126.
Interstate 95 between mile markers 141 and 146.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
